				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You typically can't use code written for one assembler with another assembler as-is.
<br />
<br />For example, I've never heard of ".mem", ".index" or ".opt" for NESASM. It's possible that they exist, but it's not something that I've ever used.
<br />
<br />Also, IIRC NESASM requires you to place some kind of whitespace (a space or a tab) before any directive (.org, .incbin, etc), otherwise it'll interpret it as a local label.</div>

